    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>It's specified by <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se8/html/jls-9.html#jls-9.6.1\" rel=\"noreferrer\">section 9.6.1 of the JLS</a>. The annotation member types must be one of:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>primitive</li>\n<li>String</li>\n<li>an Enum</li>\n<li>another Annotation</li>\n<li>java.lang.Class</li>\n<li>an array of any of the above</li>\n</ul>\n<p>It does seem restrictive, but no doubt there are reasons for it.</p>\n<p>Also note that multidimensional arrays (e.g. <code>String[][]</code>) are implicitly forbidden by the above rule.</p>\n"
  }, {
