    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The concept of annotations fits really well with the design of my project, until I realized you can't have complex datatypes in the annotation. I got around it by using the class of what I wanted to instantiate rather than an instantiated object of that class. It's not perfect, but java rarely is.</p>\n\n<pre><code>@interface Decorated { Class&lt;? extends PropertyDecorator&gt; decorator() }\n\ninterface PropertyDecorator { String decorate(String value) }\n\nclass TitleCaseDecorator implements PropertyDecorator {\n    String decorate(String value)\n}\n\nclass Person {\n    @Decorated(decorator = TitleCaseDecorator.class)\n    String name\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
